Korean Beef and Rice

Ingredients:

- 1 pound of lean ground beef (90% lean)
- 3 cloves of garlic, peeled and minced
- 1/4 cup of brown sugar, packed
- 1/4 cup of soy sauce, low sodium
- 2 teaspoons of sesame oil
- 1/4 teaspoon of ginger, ground
- 1/4 teaspoon of red pepper flakes, crushed
- 1/4 teaspoon of black pepper, ground
- 2 and 2/3 cups of brown rice, cooked and hot
- 3 green onions, sliced thinly

Directions:

1. In a large skillet over medium heat, cook the beef and garlic, breaking the beef into small pieces, for 6 to 8 minutes or until the beef is cooked through and no longer pink. Drain the excess fat if needed.
2. In a small bowl, whisk together the brown sugar, soy sauce, sesame oil, ginger, red pepper flakes, and black pepper.
3. Pour the sauce over the beef and stir to coat well.
4. Serve the beef over the rice and garnish with the green onions. Enjoy!
